# Angular 19.1.4 & Clean Code Standards

## Priority Legend
- 🔴 **Critical** - Must follow, no exceptions
- 🟠 **High** - Strong recommendation, deviate only with good reason
- 🟡 **Standard** - Expected practice
- 🟢 **Recommended** - Best practice but flexible

---

## Project Setup

- 🔴 **All components in Angular 19.1.4 are standalone by default** (no NgModules)
- 🟠 **Use typed forms with FormBuilder** when creating forms
- 🟠 **Implement signals for state management** where appropriate
- 🟡 **Follow Angular's preferred file structure**: one component per folder with component, styles, and tests
- 🟠 **Use OnPush change detection strategy** for all components

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Standalone component with OnPush strategy
@Component({
  selector: 'app-user-profile',
  templateUrl: './user-profile.component.html',
  styleUrl: './user-profile.component.scss',
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class UserProfileComponent {
  // Component logic
}

// ❌ BAD: Missing OnPush strategy
@Component({
  selector: 'app-user-profile',
  templateUrl: './user-profile.component.html',
  styleUrl: './user-profile.component.scss'
})
export class UserProfileComponent {
  // Component logic
}
```

