## Angular Specifics

- 🟠 **Use functional guards with `canActivate`** instead of class-based guards
- 🟠 **Implement route resolvers as injectable functions** using `inject()`
- 🔴 **Use typed HttpClient** with proper response interfaces
- 🔴 **Implement proper error handling with HttpClient**
- 🟠 **Use Angular signals** for component state where applicable
- 🔴 **Implement proper unsubscribe patterns** for observables
- 🟡 **Use template reference variables** over ViewChild when possible
- 🟡 **Implement content projection** with ng-content when needed
- 🟡 **Use proper attribute directives** for reusable behaviors

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Functional route guard
export const authGuard = () => {
  const router = inject(Router);
  const authService = inject(AuthService);

  return authService.isAuthenticated().pipe(
    map(isAuthenticated => isAuthenticated || router.createUrlTree(['/login']))
  );
};

// ❌ BAD: Class-based guard
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class AuthGuard {
  constructor(private router: Router, private authService: AuthService) {}

  canActivate(): Observable<boolean | UrlTree> {
    return this.authService.isAuthenticated().pipe(
      map(isAuthenticated => isAuthenticated || this.router.createUrlTree(['/login']))
    );
  }
}
```

